@node Undelete
@next Undelete
@prev Undelete
With @{FG Highlight}Undelete@{FG Text} you can recover deleted files.
After scanning the disk for deleled files you can select which files
you want to undelete by selecting the files in the listview-gadget or
by using the gadgets @{FG FillText}@{BG Fill} All @{FG Text}@{BG Background}, @{FG FillText}@{BG Fill} None @{FG Text}@{BG Background} and @{FG FillText}@{BG Fill} Recursive @{FG Text}@{BG Background}.
If you are searching a file you may switch off @{FG FillText}@{BG Fill} Tree @{FG Text}@{BG Background} and all files
will be displayed.
You can (de-)select files with @{FG FillText}@{BG Fill} Include @{FG Text}@{BG Background} and @{FG FillText}@{BG Fill} Exclude @{FG Text}@{BG Background} and
the pattern entered in the string-gadget.
After selecting the files you can use @{FG FillText}@{BG Fill} Undelete @{FG Text}@{BG Background} to copy as much as
possible from the deleted files to a slectable directory.
Use @{FG FillText}@{BG Fill} Quit @{FG Text}@{BG Background} to quit Undelete.
@endnode

@node CleanUp
@next Undelete
@prev Undelete
With @{FG Highlight}CleanUp@{FG Text} it is possible to remove the deletet files, so
that they are no longer found in Undelete/Salvage.
Undelete/Salvage will be faster and only files deleted
after Cleanup will be found.
With @{FG FillText}@{BG Fill} Restore @{FG Text}@{BG Background} you can undo @{FG FillText}@{BG Fill} CleanUp @{FG Text}@{BG Background}.
@endnode

@node Salvage
@next Salvage
@prev Salvage
@{FG Highlight}Salvage@{FG Text} is the same as @{"Undlete" link Undelete} with two exeptions:
the whole partition is scanned for files and it works even if the
partition is not validatet.
@endnode

@node Audio "Audio CD-Player"
@next Audio
@prev Audio
A simple CD Player for Audio-CDs.

@{FG FillText}@{BG Fill} 1 - 25 @{FG Text}@{BG Background} plays from the selected song to the end of the CD.
@{FG FillText}@{BG Fill} |< @{FG Text}@{BG Background} plays the previous song.
@{FG FillText}@{BG Fill} Play @{FG Text}@{BG Background} starts playing.
@{FG FillText}@{BG Fill} Stop @{FG Text}@{BG Background} stopps playing.
@{FG FillText}@{BG Fill} >| @{FG Text}@{BG Background} plays the next song.
@{FG FillText}@{BG Fill} Quit @{FG Text}@{BG Background} quits the CD-Player (but does not stop playing).

I have writte this CD-Player because @{B}no@{UB} other CD-Player works
with my CD-Drive. This CD-Player does not have much functions, if your
drive works with other players you may want to use them, besause most
other players have more functions. If your drive does not work with
other players you may try this one because it uses difrent SCSI-direct-
commands.

@{FG Highlight}Tested CD-Drives:@{FG Text}
- Amiga 4000/030, BTC CDD-157, A4000-AT-Controller + @{I}@{B}SPEEDUP @{UB}@{UI}

- Amiga 4000/040, AppleCD300 (Sony 8003), Supra SCSI Controller

- Amiga 2000/030, NEC SCSI CD-Rom drive, A2091 Controller

- Amiga 1200, Chinon CDS-545, A1200-AT-Controller + RandyRom (IDEFix)

- Mitsumi CD-Rom drive, Tandem Controller
@endnode

